  "description": "A lot of my writing recently has been focused on relational dynamics in the fields of sociology and psychology, and I thought it might be fun to look at something else: Physarum polycephalum. It\u0026rsquo;s a slime mold that\u0026rsquo;s been called the \u0026ldquo;many-headed slime,\u0026rdquo; that\u0026rsquo;s what polycephalum means. First described by Johann Heinrich Freidrich Link, a German naturalist back in 1833ce.\nI should write a history of study of Physarum polysephalum and I\u0026rsquo;m tempted to but I actually want to explain how it\u0026rsquo;s been an object of study in other fields like mass transit and logic.\n",
